## mem_per_metric_2026-05-26 — meta

### Subject

Per-metric peak GPU memory and host RSS measurement across 6 zen GPU
metric crates × 8 image sizes × (3 zensim regimes), for the umbrella
`Metric::new_with_memory_mode(_, _, _, _, MemoryMode::Full)` constructor
on the cubecl CUDA backend.

The CSV `mem_per_metric_2026-05-26.csv` is one row per cell. Each cell
runs in a fresh subprocess so cubecl's per-process memory pool starts
empty — otherwise the second metric run in the same process would
under-report by re-using the first's pool.

### Method

`crates/zenmetrics-api/examples/mem_per_metric.rs` is the harness:

- driver mode: walks the (metric, regime, w, h) grid, spawns one child
  per cell, polls `nvidia-smi --query-gpu=memory.used` every ~80 ms
  for the lifetime of the child to capture the peak `memory.used`
  delta from baseline
- child mode: constructs the metric in `Full`, runs a one-shot
  `compute_srgb_u8`, then `set_reference_srgb_u8` + two
  `compute_with_cached_reference_srgb_u8` calls. Prints `CHILD_DONE …`
  with ctor_ms, compute_ms, score, and per-process host `VmRSS` delta.

Random u8 input buffers are seeded deterministically via an xorshift64
PRNG so every cell scores the same (ref, dist) shape.

### Columns

- `metric`: butter | ssim2 | dssim | iwssim | cvvdp | zensim
- `mode`: `full` (always — this run measures Full mode only; Strip
  measurement is a follow-on)
- `regime`: `-` for all metrics except zensim; `basic` | `extended` |
  `withiw` for zensim
- `width`, `height`, `mp`: image dims
- `estimated_gpu_mb`: result of the per-crate
  `estimate_gpu_memory_bytes(w, h)` (cvvdp uses
  `estimate_gpu_memory_bytes_usize`) divided by `1024*1024`
- `baseline_gpu_mib`: `nvidia-smi memory.used` immediately before
  child spawn (MiB)
- `peak_gpu_mib`: peak `memory.used` observed by the driver's poller
  during the child's lifetime
- `peak_delta_gpu_mb`: `peak_gpu_mib - baseline_gpu_mib` (MB)
- `host_metric_mb`: child's `/proc/self/status` `VmRSS` delta from
  *after* host buffers were allocated to final. Excludes the
  reference/distorted buffers (which would otherwise add 3-4× n_bytes
  irrelevant to the metric).
- `score`: numeric score (for sanity that the kernel actually ran)
- `cached_ref_supported`: whether `set_reference_srgb_u8` returned `Ok`
- `ctor_ms`: time for `Metric::new_with_memory_mode` (includes NVRTC
  compile on first call per process)
- `compute_ms`: time for the first `compute_srgb_u8`
- `duration_s`: wall-clock time the cell took from spawn to driver
  finishing CSV append
- `status`: `ok` or `err:<message>` or `exit:<status>` on
  construct/compute errors and OOMs

### Host

- CPU: AMD Ryzen 9 7950X 16-Core Processor (water-cooled)
- RAM: 49 GiB total, 15 GiB free at start
- GPU: NVIDIA GeForce RTX 5070, 12227 MiB total VRAM, driver 596.21
- WSL2 (Linux 6.6.114.1-microsoft-standard-WSL2)
- CUDA 13.2.1 SDK at /usr/local/cuda

### GPU-baseline note

`baseline_gpu_mib` varies across cells (1047 → 1503) because cubecl /
Windows host applications around the WSL2 boundary hold ~1–5 GiB of
device memory at idle. The *delta* against the per-cell baseline is
the meaningful "this metric's footprint" number; absolute peak is
shown for completeness.

### Build

```
PATH=/usr/local/cuda/bin:$PATH \
LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/local/cuda/lib64:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH \
cargo build --release -p zenmetrics-api --example mem_per_metric \
  --features cuda,all-metrics,cubecl-types,pixels
```

### Run

```
PATH=/usr/local/cuda/bin:$PATH \
LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/local/cuda/lib64:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH \
./target/release/examples/mem_per_metric --out /tmp/mem_full.csv
```

(Full wall time: ~15 minutes including 1 stuck cell that was manually
killed; see "ssim2 8192×8192 anomaly" below.)

### git

- repo: zenmetrics
- HEAD at measurement time: 5cb6ad45bfca0b5da8065b6e711504462ea630ed
  ("docs(CHANGELOG): umbrella cached-ref + MemoryMode + VRAM probe
  unification")

### Failures recorded

- `butter 8192×8192` — estimated 12800 MB, OOM-killed mid-construct
  (peak observed 7618 MB before kernel registered the alloc; exit
  status `unix_wait_status(25856)` ≈ signal 100)
- `ssim2 8192×8192` — estimated 19963 MB. Child stalled in NVRTC for
  >2 min, manually `kill <pid>` to advance the driver. Peak observed
  10377 MB before kill. Treat as "infeasible at this size in Full
  on this GPU"; the failure mode was *slow OOM*, not clean error.
- `iwssim 64×64` — surfaces clean error: "image too small for 5-level
  IW-SSIM (min(W,H) must be ≥ 176)"

### Measurement caveats

1. `nvidia-smi memory.used` includes other processes on the host. The
   per-cell delta cancels that out only if no other process changes
   VRAM during the 80 ms poll window — which is true here because the
   measurement box is dedicated, but anywhere with concurrent users
   would need a stricter probe (e.g. CUDA's `cuMemGetInfo` from inside
   the child).
2. The 80 ms poll interval can miss spikes shorter than that. cubecl
   construction is dominated by NVRTC compile (~200ms–10s+) which
   produces flat-ish allocation. The peak should land in the visible
   range; verify against the per-crate `estimate_gpu_memory_bytes` for
   the larger-image cells where the estimate dominates init overhead.
3. The first call into cubecl per-process costs ~150–200 MB for the
   memory pool and JIT machinery. This shows up in every small-image
   cell (`peak_delta_gpu_mb` ≈ 193 MB for 64×64 across all metrics).
   Subtract this floor to get the "metric working set" — but for
   "does this fit?" purposes you want to keep the 193 MB floor in
   your VRAM budget.

### Static estimator vs measurement

In rough terms, the static estimators *under-predict* measured peaks
by a factor of 1.5× to 2.5× at small-to-mid sizes (because they don't
include the cubecl init pool + NVRTC + pinned-upload staging) and
*roughly match* measured peaks at large sizes (where the per-image
working set dominates). The largest 8K cells that succeeded landed
within ~10–20% of the estimate (cvvdp 12715 est vs 10476 measured,
zensim/withiw 6632 est vs 10290 measured — zensim's basic regime
estimator is missing the Extended/WithIw plane-budget addition,
which is documented as ~600 MB at 12 MP per scale).

zensim's `estimate_gpu_memory_bytes` does NOT take regime as input —
the 6632 MB estimate is the Basic-regime estimate; the measured 10369
MB / 10290 MB for Extended / WithIw is the additional persist-plane
cost the basic estimator misses (~600 MB/scale × 4 scales = ~2400 MB
on top of basic, consistent with what the live probe sees at 8K).
